htds

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • htds.User

  • public class User
extends java.lang.Object
    The User class is a basic data structure that stores basic information about an HTDS user. Every User has a unique ID, a username, a password and full name. Every User has a UserProfile object that specifies the access permissions for that user in HTDS Once a user is created, the id and username are fixed, but the fullName, password and UserProfileID could be updated
    Author:
    Qutaiba
